# Global Memory protocol

- Read `AGENTS.md` and `vault/INDEX.md` before memory work.
- Use `gm context "<question>" --format markdown --token-budget 1200` as the task entry. Do not load the whole vault by default.
- Preserve IDs, status, truth layer, evidence, source IDs, and uncertainty from the Context Pack.
- `vault/raw/` and canonical Markdown are durable truth. `data/indexes/`, Context Packs, and `vault/views/` are disposable views.
- Never edit canonical knowledge as an assistant write-back. Write a concise UTF-8 session receipt, then run `gm receipt create --agent cursor ...` and `gm receipt propose <receipt-id>`.
- A receipt proposal still requires the repository's normal review/approval policy.
- Do not include secrets, full chat transcripts, or unsupported inference in a receipt.
- Use `gm maintain` for read-only health/backlog checks. `--rebuild-derived` refreshes disposable indexes/views only and does not permit canonical edits.
- On Windows PowerShell, prefer `.\\scripts\\gm.ps1`; `gm` may resolve to the built-in `Get-Member` alias.

# Article import policy

- Default to cheap capture: capture the complete source, then run `.\\scripts\\gm.ps1 triage <source-id>`. This only creates/reuses extraction and quality assessment; it must not create a proposal or canonical knowledge.
- Do not run `compile`, chase primary sources, or request per-article approval merely because an article was captured.
- Use `source annotate --salience high` for an important source. Run `triage <source-id> --compile-selected` only when the user marks it important, it is needed for a current decision/output, it repeatedly appears in retrieval, or it conflicts with existing knowledge.
- A source may remain searchable as capture-only indefinitely. Verification belongs at use/promotion time; `confirmed` and canonical writes retain the existing proposal/review gate.
- For routine batches, run `triage --limit 25`; reserve cross-source synthesis, contradiction review, and expensive full-vault work for an explicit weekly maintenance session.
- Use `.\\scripts\\gm.ps1 weekly` for that weekly session. Treat its synthesis section as an eligibility report only; never infer approval or canonical authority from it.
- Prefer the configured `global-memory` MCP server for read-only context/search/show/source/status. MCP results retain the same truth-layer and approval boundaries; no MCP write tool exists.
